article.description: Kenny Hasbrouk made a jumper with a half second remaining for Siena, and Iona remained the only winless team in Division I by losing 61-60 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Iona remains only winless D-I team after loss to Siena
article.linkText: Iona falls on last-second shot, still only winless D-I team
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Kenny Hasbrouk made a jumper with a half second remaining for Siena, and Iona remained the only winless team in Division I by losing 61-60 on Thursday night. The Gaels (0-22, 0-12 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) have now lost five conference games either by one point or in overtime. Ronald Moore led Siena (12-10, 7-5) with 19 points, and Michael Haddix had 12 points and 10 rebounds. Justin Marshall scored 17 points for Iona and Mike Harris had 13. The Gaels were playing without injured leading scorer Anthony Bruin and reserve Alejo Rodriguez. Iona took a 60-59 lead, it first of the second half, with 25 seconds remaining on a short jumper by Harris. They erased a 38-26 halftime lead thanks in part to a 9-2 run following intermission. The Saints made just 3 of 12 free throws and committed 21 turnovers. Iona was 2-for-11 from 3-point range and committed 20 turnovers.
